benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request: TC01 covers successful update.
Authorization: TC02 (missing header) and TC12 (invalid/auth) cover auth scenarios.
Non-Existing Resource: TC04 handles bundle not found.
ExternalKey conflicts: TC05 covers conflict when key already used by another bundle.
Missing/Malformed Input: TC03 (malformed bundleId), TC06 (missing body), TC07 (malformed JSON), TC08 (missing externalKey).
Edge cases: TC09 (additional fields), TC10 (long externalKey), TC11 (empty externalKey), TC19 (special characters), TC20 (leading/trailing spaces).
Headers: TC14 and TC21 cover additional headers and reason/comment usage.
Regression/Backward compatibility: TC22 (legacy clients), TC18 (regression scenario with problematic key).
Performance/Other: TC23 (response time under load), TC16/TC24 cover large payload and accessibility documentation baseline.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Pagination: Not applicable to single-resource updates here; no tests for listing/pagination behavior.
Explicit Partial Update semantics: While TC09 allows extra fields, explicit test confirming only allowed fields are updated could be clearer.
Dedicated 400/500 error surface validation for server-side failures beyond integration/unavailability (e.g., DB rollback scenarios).
recommendations: Add rate limiting/throttling tests to verify system behavior under bursty traffic.
Add tests to validate caching headers and behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) on PUT responses.
If pagination should apply in related endpoints, introduce pagination tests for listing bundles; otherwise document as out of scope.
Add a focused test to confirm that only permitted fields are updated when extra fields are provided, ensuring no unintended mutations.
Include explicit server error scenarios beyond 503 (e.g., 500) to validate robust error handling on backend failures.
